
[1]sabbath-breaking

   SABBATH-BREAKING, n. A profanation of the sabbath by violating the
   injunction of the fourth commandment, or the municipal laws of a state
   which require the observance of that day as holy time. All unnecessary
   secular labor, visiting, traveling, sports, amusements and the like are
   considered as sabbath-breaking.
